OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F391A1779084318
OL,3,CBurnham says 'Manchester-ism' can
OL,4,Ctransform the whole of UK
OL,6,FBurnham is widely expected to launch a
OL,7,Fleadership challenge against Keir
OL,8,FStarmer, if he wins the by-election in
OL,9,FMakerfield later this year.
OL,11,FIn an exclusive interview with ITV
OL,12,FNews, Burnham said he wants to take
OL,13,Fthe approach he has championed in
OL,14,FGreater Manchester onto the national
OL,15,Fstage, arguing the country needs "more
OL,16,Finterventionist" politics and
OL,17,Feconomics.
OL,19,FBurnham insisted he was not abandoning
OL,20,FGreater Manchester by seeking election
OL,21,Fas an MP.
OL,26,@wD@bOUxD@PO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,392,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F391A1779084318
OL,3,CBurnham says 'Manchester-ism' can
OL,4,Ctransform the whole of UK
OL,6,F"I will never do that," he said.
OL,8,F"I am totally committed to this place
OL,9,Fand what we have done here and I am a
OL,10,Frooted person. I live literally on the
OL,11,Fdoorstep of this constituency."
OL,13,FThe Labour mayor said he believed he
OL,14,Fhad taken Greater Manchester "as far
OL,15,Fafield" as possible during almost a
OL,16,Fdecade in the role, but argued further
OL,17,Fprogress now depends on change from
OL,18,Fcentral government.
OL,26,@nD@AOUnD@WO]pD@AOUsD@_O]vD@^OUwD@GO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,392,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F391A1779084318
OL,3,CBurnham says 'Manchester-ism' can
OL,4,Ctransform the whole of UK
OL,6,F"I've come to the conclusion in my
OL,7,Falmost ten years as the Mayor of
OL,8,FGreater Manchester that I've taken the
OL,9,Fplace to as far afield as I can," he
OL,10,Fsaid.
OL,12,F"But if I want us to go to where I
OL,13,Fwant us to be, it requires more change
OL,14,Fat the national level."
OL,16,FBurnham described his political
OL,17,Fphilosophy as "Manchester-ism", saying
OL,18,Fit rejects the economic model which he
OL,19,Fclaims has failed communities like
OL,20,FMakerfield.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@aO]tD@AOUvD@WO]yD@OOUyD@^O]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/7
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,392,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F391A1779084318
OL,3,CBurnham says 'Manchester-ism' can
OL,4,Ctransform the whole of UK
OL,6,F"I talk about doing for the rest of
OL,7,Fthe country, what I have tried to do
OL,8,Ffor Greater Manchester ` Manchester-
OL,9,Fism as we call it ` and it's that more
OL,10,Finterventionist approach to the
OL,11,Feconomy," he said.
OL,13,F"People say, what is Manchester-ism?
OL,15,F"But let me answer it. It is the end
OL,16,Fof neo-liberalism. The end of trickle
OL,17,Fdown, actually, that didn't trickle
OL,18,Fmuch down to Makerfield or other
OL,19,Fplaces like it."
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@IO]uD@AOUwD@AOU{D@PO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/7
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,392,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39106
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F391A1779084318
OL,3,CBurnham says 'Manchester-ism' can
OL,4,Ctransform the whole of UK
OL,6,FThe mayor acknowledged criticism from
OL,7,Fsome who believe the by-election is
OL,8,Funnecessary, but argued it could
OL,9,Fbecome one of the most important
OL,10,Fpolitical contests in recent years.
OL,12,F"I have heard people saying that it is
OL,13,Funnecessary. I can understand why they
OL,14,Fmight say that," he said.
OL,16,F"But I would say it is the opposite. I
OL,17,Fthink this is the most consequential
OL,18,Fby-election this country has had."
OL,26,@tD@AOUvD@PO]xD@AOUzD@bO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/7
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,392,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39107
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F391A1779084318
OL,3,CBurnham says 'Manchester-ism' can
OL,4,Ctransform the whole of UK
OL,6,FHe added: "It is going to allow people
OL,7,Fto address really fundamental
OL,8,Fquestions about the way this country
OL,9,Fis being run and I think this by-
OL,10,Felection is going to allow us to let
OL,11,Fsome fresh air into British politics
OL,12,Fand have a debate that the kind of
OL,13,Fusual approach to by-elections doesn't
OL,14,Flet you have."
OL,26,@nD@KOUvD@NO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/7
